This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language understanding and sentence composition. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses neural sentence composition models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper's use of a specialized sentence generation system may also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's mention of embeddings and experiments with sentence composition models may make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
